# Guardrails Definition (Enterprise AI)

## Guardrail Categories
- Intended use / Non-use
- Human-in-the-loop requirements
- Thresholds and routing rules
- Data handling constraints (PII/PHI/confidential)
- Prompt / input constraints (if LLM)
- Output constraints (format, citations, refusal behavior)
- Escalation paths (when to stop / ask / route)
- Logging + auditability

## Minimum Guardrails Package
- Guardrails doc exists
- Misuse scenarios documented
- Kill switch defined
- Owner accountable for review cadence
